definition.value: A phosphatidylcholine 36:6 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C14:0 and C22:6 respectively.
A retinoid that is all-trans-retinoic acid which has been hydroxylated at the 4-pro-S position and at the 16 position.
A phosphatidylcholine 31:0 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as pentadecanoyl and hexadecanoyl respectively
A phosphatidylcholine 31:1 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:0 and C16:1 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 33:1 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:0 and C18:1 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 33:2 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:0 and C18:2 respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and contain a total of 33 carbons and 3 double bonds.
A phosphatidylcholine 33:2 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:0 and C18:3 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 35:4 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:0 and C20:4 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 33:2 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:1 and C18:1 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 33:3 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C15:1 and C18:2 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 32:1 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C16:1 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 33:1 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C17:1 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 34:1 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C18:1 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 34:3 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C18:3 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C20:4 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 38:5 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C22:5 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 38:6 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C22:6 respectively.
A phosphatidylcholine 39:5 in which the fatty acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as C16:0 and C23:5 respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl and 7-oxoheptanoyl respectively.

An azaspiro compound resulting from the formal fusion of position 3 of 6-chloro-oxindole with position 3 of (2R,3SS5S)-3-(3-chloro-2-fluorophenyl)-5-(2,2-dimethylpropyl)-N-[2-(morpholin-4-yl)ethyl]pyrrolidine-2-carboxamide. It is a potent inhibitor of the MDM2-p53 interaction.
A 1-acyl-2-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl and alkyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as hexadecanoyl and hexadecyl respectively.
A lysophosphatidylcholine 16:1 in which the acyl group is located at position 1.
Any organic heterotricyclic compound with a skeleton consisting of a diazepine ring fused to an indole.
An N-glycosylpyrrolopyrimidine that is tubercidin in which the hydrogen at position 5 of the pyrrolopyrimidine moiety has been replaced by a cyano group.
A member of the class of menaquinones that is menaquinone-9 in which the double bond that is second nearest to the naphthoquinone moiety has been dihydrogenated.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is (4Z,9E,11E,13Z,15E,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid having an epoxy group across positions 7 and 8 as well as a hydroxy substituent at the 17S-position.
A nitrosamine that is iminodiacetone that is substituted by a nitroso group at the N-atom. It induces pancreatic ductal adenocarcinomas in Syrian golden hamsters (other rodents are not susceptible).

A tricarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the three carboxy groups and protonation of the secondary amino group of N-[(2S)-2-amino-2-carboxyethyl]-L-glutamic acid. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A siderophore composed from L-2,3-diaminopropionic acid, citric acid, 1,2-diaminoethane and alpha-ketoglutaric acid units.
A octadecanoid that is any octadecenoic acid carrying a single hydroperoxy substituent (position unspecified).

A member of the class of thiocyanates that is methane in which two of the hycrogens have been replaced by thiocyanato groups. Used as a biocide for the control of various pathogens and algae in industrial water systems and as a fungicide for the control of surface moulds and sapstain fungi on wood.
A octadecanoid that is any octadecatrienoic acid carrying a single hydroperoxy substituent (position unspecified).
An S-substituted glutathione(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the the two carboxy groups and protonation of the amino group of 2-(glutathion-S-yl)hydroquinone; major species at pH 7.3.
An epoxy fatty acid consisting of stearic (octadecanoic) acid with a single epoxide in an unspecified position.
A leukotriene that is (5S,7E,9E,11Z)-5-hydroxyicosa-7,9,11-trienoic acid in which a glutathionyl group is attached at position 6 via a sulfide linkage.
A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue is attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-[omega-(linoleoyloxy)]acyl-sphing-4E-enine.

A diastereoisomeric mixture of (2S,4R)- and (2S,4S)- hypoglycin A, found in the edible part of the fruit of the Ackee, Blighia sapida (where the 2S,4R diastereoisomer is more dominant (17% d.e.) than its 2S,4S counterpart) as well as in the sycamore maple tree (Acer pseudoplatanus).
A C14 straight-chain saturated fatty acid where the aliphatic hydrogens have been replaced by deuterium atoms.
A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue is attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-[omega-(9R)-hydroperoxy-(10E,12Z)-octadecadienoyloxy]acyl-sphing-4E-enine.
A D-glucose in which the six carbon atoms have been replaced by the (13)C isotope.
A beta-D-glucosylceramide in which a beta-D-glucosyl residue is attached to the primary hydroxyl group of N-[omega-(9R,10R)-epoxy-(13R)-hydroxy-(11E)-octadecadienoyloxy]acyl-sphing-4E-enine.
A leukotriene that is (5S,7E,9E,11Z)-5-hydroxyicosa-7,9,11-trienoic acid in which an L-cysteinylglycinyl group is attached at position 6R via a sulfide linkage.
An (E)-2-methylbutanal oxime that has S configuration at position 2.
A (Z)-2-methylbutanal oxime that has S configuration at position 2.
A 2-methylbutyronitrile that has S configuration.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of any L-polyhomomethionine; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-polyhomomethionine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-dihomomethionine; major species at pH 7.3.
An L-polyhomomethionine zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-trihomomethionine; major species at pH 7.3.
